<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Pretty sucky stats and AC for something worth 900pp?<BR>
 <BR>
          WHY THE $#@! ARE THESE SO EXPENSIVE?<BR>
  <BR>
   My Rogue wears Elf-hide gloves, AC4 +5 dex +5 agility and only worth 100 or so pp. True they are bard/rogue only, but I don't understand how these gauntlets can be so expensive even if they are rare. Anyone care to enlighten my little gnomish brain?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Klymeth</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-08 13:10:08</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The reason these gauntlets are so expensive is twofold.<BR>
<BR>
First, they are a very rare item. Therefore, they are expensive, reguardless of stats.<BR>
<BR>
Secondly, these gauntlets are ALL/ALL. With the weight and magic properties, many monks will pay very well for them. And with the AC and bonuses, pure casters love them as well.<BR>
<BR>
I am not sure they are worth the thousands of PP that some would suggest. However, I recently completed the quest, and gladly trade them for the golden cleric-quest chestplate. <BR>
<BR>
Klymeth D'Silthri<BR>
Priest of Tunare<BR>
Realm of Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table>
