<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Alector</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-28 23:22:23</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Weight is definitely 0.2, that's what makes them so attractive to monks - apparently these are the best non-planar, non-kunark gloves available to monks.<BR>
I was really lucky on this one, a warrior who killed the werewolf was asking the zone what to do with the werewolf claw, I answered that it was for a quest in everfrost, but being unclear myself on the details, couldn't help him much.  So I bought the claw from him for 24pp (all the money I had with me), ringed to NK and ran the rest of the way.<BR>
I logged in Everfrost, and checked the quest details - that was when I found out how much this gauntlet is worth - 1000pp item for an outlay of 99pp (75+24).<BR>
Did the quest, and a wizard who was just 1 step slower than me offered to trade his werewolf claw and a lizard scale mantle for the gauntlets, so I took the deal, found Karg again the next RL day and traded in for the second set.</font></td></tr></table>
